data.text:
Martin Moszkowicz (born April 25, 1958) is a German film producer.[1] Moszkowicz is the Chairman of the Executive Board at Constantin Film.[2] On March 6, 2019, Martin Moszkowicz was appointed Honorary Professor at University of Television and Film Munich.[3]

As producer, executive producer, co-producer he has been involved in well over 300 nationally and internationally successful feature films and numerous television shows. Recent projects include Resident Evil: The Final Chapter, Fack ju GÃ¶hte 3, This Crazy Heart, How About Adolf?, Polar, The Collini Case, The Silence, Das perfekte Geheimnis, Dragon Rider and Monster Hunter.[4]
